                        <idno/>
                    </msIdentifier>
                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            Four lists of <foreign>biruda</foreign>s engraved of the <foreign>prākāra</foreign> of the Rājasiṃheśvara temple, that is, on four tiers of the base of the chapels (also designated as cells or shrines in secondary literature) and of the western entrance. 
                            The lists of the first three tiers are the same except for the script (plain Siddhamātr̥kā for the first list, plain Grantha for the second list, ornate Grantha for the third list) and some minor variants. There are four <foreign>biruda</foreign>s per chapel, except for chapels 20, western entrance and chapel 39.
                            The list on the fourth and lower tier is in ornate Siddhamātr̥kā script (see also inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSPallava00385.xml">Pallava 385</ref> on the base of the <foreign>prākāra</foreign> of the Mahendreśvara). It is shorter since its ornate Siddhamātr̥kā requires more space that the scripts of the other lists. Only the chapels nos. 1-3 and 5-21 are inscribed on the fourth tier.
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p/>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
